{"word":"ὅστε","slug":"ὅστε","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n75588\" key=\"o(/ste\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὅστε</orth>, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἥτε, ὅτε</foreign> (also written divisim), in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl> also <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὅ τε</orth> as masc., <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:17:757\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">17.757</biblScope> </bibl> : (<etym lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"etym\">ὅς, τε</etym>):—<sense id=\"n75588.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">who, which,</tr_> <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">like</abbr> the simple <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅς</foreign> or <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅστις,</foreign> freq. with a generalizing force (<itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">τε</itype> is however sts. otiose, as in <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὅτε, ὥστε, οἷός τε, ἐπεί τε,</foreign> etc., <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">τε</itype> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ B.\">B.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1</biblScope> </bibl>), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:14:221\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.221</biblScope></bibl>, etc.: neut. pl. <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">τά τε</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:5:481\" default=\"NO\" TEI